        <content><![CDATA[    <h1 class="title topictitle1">Email listeners</h1>            <div class="body taskbody"><p class="shortdesc">You can setup email listeners that process emails sent to ServiceNow from third party        monitoring tools. </p>        <div class="section prereq p">            <p class="p">Your ServiceNow instance can send email notifications for specific system events,                such as updates to incidents or change requests. To support notifications, the                default email configuration includes a POP3 mailbox on a ServiceNow email server and                a ServiceNowSMTP server to process outbound email messages.</p>            <p class="p">To test email notifications, enter a comma-separated list of email addresses in the                Send all email to this test email address (non-production testing) field.</p>        </div>        <div class="li step p">                <span class="ph cmd">To setup email listeners, click <span class="ph uicontrol">New</span>.</span>            </div>    </div>]]></content>
